Pleasing to the eye or mind especially through beauty or charm.
Lacking beauty or charm; not appealing to the senses.
Not often.
Problem associated with facility not providing satisfactory initial and/or periodic user training covering operation of a medical device.

label.value: Device Unsafe to Use in Environment

value.value: Problem associated with environmental condition that results in the unsafe use of the device. (e.g. electromagnetic fields, noise, vibration, microbiological contamination etc.).
A slender, hollow needle used for injection or aspiration.
Lymphoblastic lymphoma that affects the spleen.
The thickness of a wire or a similarly shaped object.
This gene may be involved in the proliferation of T-cells.

Human CD5 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 11q13 and is approximately 25 kb in length. This allele, which encodes T-cell surface glycoprotein CD5 protein, may play a role in the modulation of T-cell proliferation.
A mixture of cells possessing a single nucleus, including monocytes and lymphocytes; blood leukocytes from which granulocytes have been separated and removed.
T-cell surface glycoprotein CD5 (495 aa, ~54 kDa) is encoded by the human CD5 gene. This protein may be involved in regulating the proliferation of T-cells.
Red blood cells that are at the last stage of development, still containing a nucleus, that are found in the bone marrow and occasionally in the peripheral blood.
The cellular material of blood consisting of white blood cells and nucleated red blood cells.
This gene plays a role in cell-cell adhesion.

Human CD6 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 11q13 and is approximately 49 kb in length. This allele, which encodes T-cell differentiation antigen CD6 protein, is involved in the regulation of cellular adhesion and may be associated with T-cell maturation.
T-cell differentiation antigen CD6 (668 aa, ~72 kDa) is encoded by the human CD6 gene. This protein plays a role in the adherence of immature thymus cells to thymic epithelial cells.

A non-metastasizing neoplasm that arises from the ovary and is characterized by the presence of neoplastic epithelium that resembles the epithelium of the fallopian tube. There is no evidence of atypia.  It includes serous cystadenoma, serous adenofibroma, serous cystadenofibroma, and surface papilloma.

A proprietary nutritional supplement with potential male sexual function enhancement effect. L-Arginine/American ginseng/Korean ginseng/Ginkgo biloba-based supplement incorporates a standardized combination of Ginkgo biloba (24% flavone glycosides, 6% terpene lactones), Korean ginseng (Panax ginseng -30% ginsenosides), American ginseng (Panax quinquefolius - 5% ginsenosides), L-Arginine, along with vitamins B6, B12, folate, thiamin, riboflavin, niacin, biotin, pantothenic acid, vitamins A, C, E, selenium, and zinc. L-Arginine is a precursor for nitric oxide (NO); ginseng may facilitate the conversion of L-Arginine into NO by NO synthase; the natural herb Ginkgo biloba may promote microvascular circulation. Overall, this supplement may increase NO production, which leads to vasodilatation and enhanced circulation. The improved blood flow is critical for sexual function and arousal.

A synthetic glucopyranoside with antithrombotic activity. Fondaparinux selectively binds to antithrombin III, thereby potentiating the innate neutralization of activated factor X (Factor Xa) by antithrombin. Neutralization of Factor Xa inhibits its activity and interrupts the blood coagulation cascade, thereby preventing thrombin formation and thrombus development.
A first-generation cyclopentyl-containing sulfonylurea with hypoglycemic activity. Tolpentamide was never marketed.
A C-C Chemokine Receptor Type 5 (CCR5) antagonist with activity against human immunodeficiency virus (HIV). Maraviroc inhibits HIV-1 entry via CCR5 coreceptor interaction.

A maleate salt form of Vicriviroc, a piperazine-based CCR5 receptor antagonist with activity against human immunodeficiency virus. Vicriviroc is designed to bind to CCR5 and inhibit the entry of HIV into CD4 cells.

A non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor. Emivirine has a structure typical of a nucleoside analog but has been shown to bind directly to the reverse transcriptase and act as an NNRTI. However, it is no longer in development due to the fact that it causes an increasingly rapid breakdown of other drugs metabolized by the cytochrome P450 enzyme.
A mesylate salt form of atevirdine, a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor. Atevirdine is active against AZT-resistant virus strains.

label.value: Borderline Ovarian Serous Surface Papillary Tumor

value.value: A neoplasm of low malignant potential arising from the ovary. It is characterized by the presence of papillary proliferations that contain atypical serous epithelial cells in the outer surface of the ovary.  There is no evidence of stromal invasion.
